40|$|This Note {{examines}} how differences in U. S. and German variants of federalism {{have contributed to}} the formation and development of <b>the</b> dual <b>banking</b> <b>system</b> in <b>the</b> United States and <b>the</b> three-pillar <b>banking</b> <b>system</b> in Germany. Specifically, this Note considers the manner in which federalism has informed <b>the</b> respective <b>banking</b> <b>systems</b> 2 ̆ 7 reactions to dynamic changes in <b>the</b> global <b>banking</b> industry and analyzes the role federalism has played in contributing to or impeding reform efforts in the United States and Germany...|$|R
